
####
Active Job creates the job into ruby hash and pushes it to queue adapter


####

Sidekiq serializes to JSON

Sidekiq now:

Adds Sidekiq-specific metadata

Converts everything to JSON

Pushes it into Redis

####
Sidekiq pushes job to Redis

####

	what happens if something fails?
	Example: Email service down

	Sidekiq:

	Catches exception
	Retries job automatically
	Uses exponential backoff
	Stores retry info in Redis

	You get:

	Automatic retries
	Failure tracking
	Dead jobs queue

####

	Rails server / Sidekiq process crashes üî•

	Important distinction:

	‚ùå Rails web server restart (Puma)
	‚úÖ Sidekiq is a separate process

	But assuming Sidekiq itself crashes or is restarted:

	Job never gets acknowledged

	Sidekiq does NOT delete the job

	Redis still knows: this job was being worked on

####

| Redis structure | Purpose                     |
| --------------- | --------------------------- |
| `queue:*`       | Waiting jobs                |
| `processes`     | Active Sidekiq processes    |
| `workers`       | Currently running jobs      |
| `retry`         | Failed jobs with retry      |
| `dead`          | Jobs that exhausted retries |
| `scheduled`     | Jobs scheduled in future    |


